    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-24T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-24T06:00:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/691: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the American Representation on the Preparatory
                        Commission</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-24T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1928—12 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 25—5:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. My 20, March 24, 4 p.m. Cushendun’s letter handed me during final afternoon
                    session of Commission and came as complete surprise. Cushendun and Admiral Kelly
                    left immediately afterwards for London, so I had no opportunity to discuss
                    proposals or learn why they were presented here.</p>
                <p>We have declined to discuss matter with press and have taken the stand that
                    comment must come from Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
